specimens.fieldNotes: NOTEBY J. Longino, NOTEDATE 3-Jan-07: Jason Grant corresponded with me, starting in Nov 2006, regarding ants he found in live stems of a new gentian species he was describing. This collection was found in hollow live stems. The stem is about 2cm diameter, with preformed cavities separated by septa. The drawing in his letter looked like the inside of Triplaris. He said the ants bore a hole into the cavity; there are no preformed holes into the cavity.
